org.modelio.gproject.gproject

Interface IProjectFactory

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    GRemoteProjectFactory, GUrlProjectFactory

    public interface IProjectFactory
    Interface that all project factories must implement.

    • Method Detail

      • createProject

        GProject createProject(ProjectDescriptor projectDescriptor)
                throws IllegalArgumentException
        Instantiate a GProject from a descriptor.

        The implementation should just create an instance of GProject and return.

        Parameters:
        projectDescriptor - a project descriptor
        Returns:
        the built GProject.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the descriptor is not supported.

      • supports

        boolean supports(ProjectDescriptor projectDescriptor)
        Tells whether the given project descriptor is supported.
        Parameters:
        projectDescriptor - a project descriptor
        Returns:
        true if the factory can create a project with it, else false.

      • getRemoteDescriptor

        ProjectDescriptor getRemoteDescriptor(ProjectDescriptor projectDescriptor,
                                      IAuthData authData,
                                      IModelioProgress monitor)
                               throws IOException,
                                      GProjectAuthenticationException
        Get the remote project descriptor.

        Should return null for local projects.

        Parameters:
        projectDescriptor - the local descriptor of the project.
        authData - authentication data.
        monitor - the progress monitor to use for reporting progress to the user. It is the caller's responsibility to call done() on the given monitor. Accepts null, indicating that no progress should be reported and that the operation cannot be cancelled.
        Returns:
        the remote project descriptor
        Throws:
        IOException - in case of failure.
        GProjectAuthenticationException - in case of authentication failure.
